{"lemma":"فَرْقُ","slug":"فَرْقُ","root":"ف.ر.ق","root_slug":"ف-ر-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ر-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فَرْق","root":"فرق","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":8,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":28},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33664","n33666","n33667","n33668","n33669"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D9%82%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to split, separate","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to part the hair"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to distinguish"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to expound, explain"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to determine, order, ordain"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to separate","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be spaced far apart, to be gappy (of teeth)","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have a split crest (of a rooster)","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to enter a group (of a person)","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be parted (of one's forelock or beard)","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be have uneven hips (of an animal)","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to stand with legs apart (of a camel)","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have far-separated horns or testicles (of a goat)","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have only one testicle (of a horse)","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to separate","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to distinguish","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to disperse","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to divide (something) between","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَرَقَ (faraqa, “to separate”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","intransitive","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَرَقَ (faraqa, “to separate”) (form I); separation","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"difference","tags":["intransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"منذ صغرنا، نقدر أن نميِّز الفرق بين التصرفات العادلة والظالمة.","english":"From a young age, we are able to distinguish between just and unjust actions."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"discord","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"parting of the hair","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of فِرْقَة (firqa)","tags":["form-of","intransitive","plural"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fear, to be afraid","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be terrified","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to feel sorry","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَرِقَ (fariqa, “to fear”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","intransitive","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/fa.ra.qa/","/fa.ri.qa/","/far.ra.qa/","/farq/","/fi.raq/","/fa.raq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33664","headword_ar":"فَرْقٌ","root":"frq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[is originally an inf. n.: but is often used as a simple subst. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A distinction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difference,"},{"kind":"text","text":"between two things. ―         -b2-  Hence,] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"line"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"division"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the hair of the head:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K: [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maforaqN","text_ar":"مَفْرَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or, as some say, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the head,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extending from the side of the forehead to the spiral curl upon the crown:"},{"kind":"text","text":"an ex. occurs in a verse of Aboo-Dhu-eyb cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTorabN","text_ar":"مَطْرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  [And app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A blaze on a horse's forehead."},{"kind":"text","text":"(See an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEotadilN","text_ar":"مُعْتَدِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)] ―         -b4-  And [hence, perhaps,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAnato fiY qa*aAlihi furuwqN mina Al$~ayobi","text_ar":"بَانَتْ فِى قَذَالِهِ فُرُوقٌ مِنَ الشَّيْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awoDaAHN","text_ar":"اَوْضَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There appeared in the back of his head portions of white,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hoary, hair, distinct from the rest"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b5-  One says also of the female comber and dresser of the hair,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamo$uiTu ka*aA waka*aA faroqFA","text_ar":"تَمْشُِطُ كَذَا وَكَذَا فَرْقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She combs and dresses"},{"kind":"text","text":"the hair]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with such and such a mode"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of combing and dressing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of dividing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L. [But the last word, which seems to be in this case an inf. n., is there written without any vowel-sign.])       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain bird"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flying thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAy^irN","text_ar":"طَايِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"O, K;) not mentioned by AHát in “ the Book of Birds. ” (O, TA.)       -A3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Flax."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraqN","text_ar":"فَرَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in nine places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n33666","headword_ar":"فِرْقٌ","root":"frq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion, that is split from a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cleft therefrom;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K;) whence its usage in the Kur xxvi. 63: (S, O:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a portion of anything"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it is separated;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firaqN","text_ar":"فِرَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a portion that is separated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispersed, of a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and thus it is said to mean in the Kur ubi suprá; and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforaAqN","text_ar":"اَفْرَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHomaAlN","text_ar":"اَحْمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HimolN","text_ar":"حِمْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firoqapN","text_ar":"فِرْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A great flock"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herd, of sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) and (as some say, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the bovine kind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of gazelles:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats, only:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of straying sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariyqN","text_ar":"فَرِيقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariyqapN","text_ar":"فَرِيقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"less than a hundred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firoqaAni mino TayorK SawaAf~a","text_ar":"فِرْقَانِ مِنْ طَيْرٍ صَوَافَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad., in which the second and third chapters of the Kur-án are likened thereto, (L,) means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two flocks"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of birds expanding their wings without moving them in flight"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L, TA: but the first word, in both, is without any vowel-sign.) See, again,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firoqapN","text_ar":"فِرْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A set of boys."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) An"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2385},{"kind":"text","text":"Arab of the desert said of some boys whom he saw,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`w^ulaA='i firoqu sawo'K","text_ar":"هٰوُلَا=ءِ فِرْقُ سَوْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"These are a bad set of boys"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A distinct quantity of date-stones with which the camel is fed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b5-  [And app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any feed"},{"kind":"text","text":"for one's beast: see an ex. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jl","text_ar":"جل"},{"kind":"text","text":", conj. 4.]       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mountain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O, K.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hill,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mountain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, such as is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haDobap","text_ar":"هَضْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, O, K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wave, billow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surge."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O, K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfiroqu","text_ar":"الفِرْقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name applied by the Arabs to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The star"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the right shoulder of Cepheus."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kzw.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA","L"]},{"entry_id":"n33667","headword_ar":"فَرَقٌ","root":"frq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wideness of the space between the two central incisors,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKh, S, O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and likewise"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the two toe-nails of the camel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Yaakoob, S, O, K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A division in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eurof","text_ar":"عُرْف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comb"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the cock:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and likewise"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the forelock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the beard, of a man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforaAqN","text_ar":"اَفْرَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sparseness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a scattered state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the plants, or herbage, of a land. (S, O, K.) ―         -b2-  In a horse, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state of the hips when one of them is more prominent than the other;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is disapproved: (S, O, K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a deficiency in one of the thighs, in comparison with the other:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a deficiency in one of the hips."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dawn:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfaraqu","text_ar":"الفَرَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falaqu","text_ar":"فَلَقُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~uboHi","text_ar":"الصُّبْحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what has broken of the bright gleam of dawn; of the dawn that rises and spreads, filling the horizon with its whiteness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@nofalaqa mino Eamuwdi AlS~uboHi","text_ar":"ا@نْفَلَقَ مِنْ عَمُودِ الصُّبْحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is one of the explanations of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfalaqu","text_ar":"الفَلَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the K];) because it has become separated from the blackness of the night: (TA:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboyanu mino faraqi AlS~uboHi","text_ar":"اَبْيَنُ مِنْ فَرَقِ الصُّبْحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falaqi","text_ar":"فَلَقِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~uboHi","text_ar":"الصُّبْحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More distinct than what has broken of the bright gleam of dawn"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O, Msb, * TA.)       -A2-  It is also the inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariqa","text_ar":"فَرِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.: when used as a simple subst., signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fright"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O, Msb.)       -A3-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroqN","text_ar":"فَرْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K,) the latte accord. to the usage of the relaters of traditions, (Az, Mgh, O, Msb, TA,) but the former accord. to the usage of the Arabs, (Az, Mgh, O, * TA,) or the former is the more chaste (K, TA) accord. to Ahmad Ibn-Yahyà and Khálid Ibn-Yezeed, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain vessel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Mgh, O, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a measure of capacity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of large size,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in El-Medeeneh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"holding three"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=SuE","text_ar":"ا=صُع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAEN","text_ar":"صَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Mgh, O, Msb, K, TA,) or, (K, [app. referring to ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroqN","text_ar":"فَرْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"only,]) which is the same quantity,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sixteen pints,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K, * TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twelve times the quantity termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mud~","text_ar":"مُدّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the people of El-Hijáz:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or, accord. to El-Kutabee, the ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroq","text_ar":"فَرْق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sixteen pints,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SAE","text_ar":"صاع"},{"kind":"text","text":"is one third of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroq","text_ar":"فَرْق"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraq","text_ar":"فَرَق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eighty pints:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroq","text_ar":"فَرْق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", he adds, is, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"four pints:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"four"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arobaAE","text_ar":"اَرْبَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruboEN","text_ar":"رُبْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]; (K, TA;) thus accord. to AHát: and IAth says, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraq","text_ar":"فَرَق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"five"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqosaAT","text_ar":"اَقْسَاط"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"six;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qisoTN","text_ar":"قِسْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";)] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qisoT","text_ar":"قِسْط"},{"kind":"text","text":"being the half of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SAE","text_ar":"صاع"},{"kind":"text","text":": but the ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroq","text_ar":"فَرْق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hundred and twenty pints:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) in the “ Nawádir ” of Hishám, on the authority of [the Imám] Mohammad, the ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroq","text_ar":"فَرْق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thirty-six pints;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but [Mtr says] this I have not found in any of the lexicons in my possession; and so what is said in the Moheet, that it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sixty pints:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furoqaAnN","text_ar":"فُرْقَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, O, K, TA,) which is of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroqN","text_ar":"فَرْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraqN","text_ar":"فَرَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mgh, O, TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforuqN","text_ar":"اَفْرُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in a trad. as a pl. [of pauc.] of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraqN","text_ar":"فَرَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning the measure thus called. (TA.) 'Áïsheh is related to have said that she and the Prophet used to wash themselves from a vessel called the ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroq","text_ar":"فَرْق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, Msb.) [In a verse of which a hemistich is cited in the S and TA, the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furoqaAn","text_ar":"فُرْقَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Milking-vessels."},{"kind":"text","text":"(See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfuroqu","text_ar":"الفُرْقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) Respecting a modern signification of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroq","text_ar":"فَرْق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bale,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sack,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of merchandise), see De Sacy's Chrest. Ar., sec. ed., iii., 378-9 and 382.]"}],"source_refs":["IKh","S","O","K","TA","Mgh","Msb","Az","T"]},{"entry_id":"n33668","headword_ar":"فَرُقٌ","root":"frq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faruwqapN","text_ar":"فَرُوقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n33669","headword_ar":"فَرِقٌ","root":"frq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to plants, or herbage, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabotN","text_ar":"نَبْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) as meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In a sparse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scattered, state;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small, not covering the ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, K, TA:) or (K)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariqapN","text_ar":"فَرِقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to land, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage, are in a sparse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scattered, state;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not contiguous:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA:) thus used, it is a possessive epithet, having no verb. (TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faruwqapN","text_ar":"فَرُوقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":["AHn","K","TA","S","O"]}]}}